               <msContents>
                  <summary>A composite volume containing two short works by <persName
                        key="person_9878408" role="aut">the Báb</persName>: (1) a commentary on the
                     Qur'anic Súratu'l-'Asr (Q. 103), written in response to a challenge from the
                     Imám-Jum'a of Isfahán; and (2) a second, untitled work, described by Browne as
                     an answer to a letter of enquiry, containing the "Doxology of Fátima"
                     (Tasbíh-i-Fátima) and ending with a short explanation of Súratu't-Takáthur (Q.
                     102).</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="F_9-item1" n="1">
                     <locus from="1b" to="87b">ff. 1b-87b (f. 88a blank)</locus>
                     <author key="person_9878408" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/9878408/">
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Bāb, ʻAlī Muḥammad
                           Shīrāzī, 1819-1850</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar">باب، ميرزا علي محمد</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="work_1585">Tafsīr sūrat al-ʻaṣr</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_1585">تفسير سورة العصر</title>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="desc">Commentary on the Súratu'l-'Asr</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar" cert="low" resp="#ocr-draft">بسم الله الرحمن الرحیم
                        الحمد لله الُذى جلّی للممکنات بظهور اثار ابداعه فى ملکوت ظهورات آیات الملکوت
                        ليشهد الكل فى کل مقامات المر و آیات الغتم... (f. 2b)</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar" cert="low" resp="#ocr-draft">... سبحان ربک رب العزه عما
                        یصفون و سلام علی المرسلین و الحمد لله رب العالمین (ff. 87a-87b)</explicit>
                     <note>Browne states the occasion of the Báb's writing this commentary is
                        described in the <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_1842">Tárikh-i-Jadíd</title>
                        (citing <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_626">BBP.
                           5, f. 106a</ref> , and British Library Or. 2942, ff. 103a-103b): the
                        Imám-Jum'a of Isfahán, testing the Báb's claim, asked him to write a
                        commentary on Súratu'l-'Asr as he had previously written one on
                        Súratu'l-Kawthar for Áqá Seyyid Yahyá of Dárab; the Báb reportedly wrote a
                        thousand sentences every three hours. Browne quotes the Tárikh-i-Jadíd's
                        account of this in English translation and gives a further Arabic extract
                        (ff. 4b-5b) in which he finds an allusion to the request.</note>
                     <note>Browne remarks in a footnote on "the humble tone of this passage, as well
                        as the absence of all claim to infallibility," taking it as evidence the
                        work belongs to an earlier period of the Báb's writing.</note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>
                           <ref target="https://cudl.lib.cam.ac.uk/view/PR-A-00233-00004/85"
                              >p.59</ref>
                        </bibl>
                        <bibl>See Browne's "Catalogue and Description of 27 Bābī Manuscripts
                           (Continuation)", in Journal of the Royal Asiatic Society of Great Britain
                           and Ireland (Oct., 1892): 637-710.</bibl>
                        <bibl type="text-relations"/>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="F_9-item2" n="2">
                     <locus from="88b" to="99a">ff. 88b-98a (ff. 98b-99a blank)</locus>
                     <author key="person_9878408" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/9878408/">
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Bāb, ʻAlī Muḥammad
                           Shīrāzī, 1819-1850</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="en" key="person_9878408">The Bab</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar">باب، ميرزا علي محمد</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="supplied">Answer to a letter of enquiry, containing
                        the Tasbíh-i-Fátima</title>
                     <title xml:lang="en" type="desc" key="">Doxology of Fátima</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar" cert="low" resp="#ocr-draft">بسم الله العلى العظيم اسبح
                        سبحان الذی لم یعلم جوهر وجود کیف هو... (begins f. 88b; preface proper begins
                        f. 93b, l. 2)</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar" cert="low" resp="#ocr-draft">... کلا سوف تعلمون ثم کلا
                        سوف تعلمون کلا لو تعلمون علم الیقین... و سلام علی المرسلین و الحمد لله رب
                        العالمین (ff. 97b-98a, ending with a short explanation of Súratu't-Takáthur,
                        Q. 102)</explicit>
                     <note>Browne identifies this as answering "a letter of enquiry" (per a passage
                        on <locus from="93v" to="93v">f. 93b</locus>) and as containing the "Doxology of Fátima" alluded to by his
                        correspondent. In a footnote he suggests the allusion on f. 94a is to Mullá
                        Ḥuseyn of Bushraweyh.</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
