                     key="person_266910202">Ṣubḥ-i Azal</persName> but transmitted through him
                     from Persia, along with <ref
                        target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_640">F. 6 (BBF.
                        7)</ref>, <ref target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_576">F.
                           10 (BBF. 8)</ref>, and <ref
                              target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_582">F. 16 (BBF.
                              9)</ref>. by an anonymous correspondent from <placeName key="place_8904936"
                                 >Tehran</placeName> to <placeName key="place_7880092">Cyprus</placeName> and
                     from there to <placeName key="place_7002445">England</placeName> via <persName
                        key="person_2387160245386552640008"
                        ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/http://viaf.org/viaf/2387160245386552640008"
                        role="oth"> Captain Arthur Young (1854-1938)</persName>
                     <!--WikiID Q4800773--> and received by E.G.Browne in <date when="1890">8
                        December 1890</date>.</provenance>
                  <acquisition when="1936">Passed to <placeName>Cambridge</placeName> University
                     Library in <date when="1936">1936 </date>(the "Browne
                     Bequest").</acquisition>
               </history>
